INSERT IGNORE INTO REVIEW  (user_id, game_id, rating, review_text, recommended, helpful_count, likes_count, created_date) VALUES
(1043, 29, 3, 'ExterminateError (The QA Tester): Outer Wilds offers a unique exploration experience with its intricate puzzle mechanics. However, I noticed a few minor bugs that occasionally detract from the immersion. Overall, it''s a fascinating game but requires a bit more polish to meet top QA standards.', TRUE, 0, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 137 DAY)),
(1005, 29, 4, 'TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter): I''m captivated by the mysteries of Outer Wilds, but I was relieved to find there are no multiplayer achievements to worry about. The solo achievement experience is well-crafted and rewarding!', TRUE, 18, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 306 DAY)),
(1013, 29, 3, 'GlitchGuru (The QA Tester): Outer Wilds is an intriguing game with a captivating narrative. I did come across some glitches during my playthrough, but none were game-breaking. It''s clear the developers put a lot of effort into crafting a mesmerizing universe.', TRUE, 3, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 55 DAY)),
(1047, 29, 2, 'FPSFanatic (The Performance Purist): Outer Wilds is a visually stunning game, but I did experience some frame rate drops in certain areas which disrupted the otherwise seamless exploration. Some optimization updates would really enhance the experience.', FALSE, 11, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 136 DAY)),
(1028, 29, 5, 'JoystickJuggler (The Controller User): Outer Wilds is a joy to play with a controller, providing smooth and immersive navigation through space. I appreciated the intuitive controller mapping, making exploration feel natural and engaging.', TRUE, 8, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 134 DAY)),
(1006, 30, 1, 'ReturnRebel (The Refund Rager): I don''t get the hype. Return of the Obra Dinn is one of those games where I found myself asking why I even bothered. The monochrome visuals are hard on the eyes, and the constant backtracking with little reward is infuriating. I can''t believe I wasted my time AND money on this. Honestly, just give me my refund already!', FALSE, 4, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 47 DAY)),
(1025, 30, 3, 'MissedOpportunity (The FOMO Victim): I went into Return of the Obra Dinn after hearing all the buzz, hoping to catch the wave before it died down. While the concept and storytelling were interesting, I didn''t feel the same thrill that everyone else seems to. It''s clever, sure, but it didn''t grip me like I expected. I''m neutral because maybe I just missed what others are raving about.', TRUE, 2, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY)),
(1038, 30, 2, 'ConsoleCommander (The Controller User): Oh man, Return of the Obra Dinn would have been a completely different experience if it had proper controller support. Navigating with a keyboard and mouse was cumbersome and took away from the experience. For someone like me who''s used to the smooth feel of a controller, this game was a real struggle. I ended up frustrated more often than not.', FALSE, 4, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 84 DAY)),
(1045, 30, 2, 'ResolutionRadical (The Graphics Snob): Ugh, Return of the Obra Dinn looks like it was made in the early 90s, and not in a charming retro way. This ''dated'' visual style is just not my cup of tea. Sure, it might be ''artistic'', but give me modern graphics engines any day. It''s hard to immerse in a game when I''m distracted by how old everything looks.', FALSE, 7, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1017, 30, 4, 'MegaWhale (The Whale): Customization is my game, and while Return of the Obra Dinn doesn''t offer much in that department, I found myself surprisingly captivated by its unique style. The detective work and painstaking detail in the narrative are incredible, and there''s something special about unraveling the mystery piece by piece. It''s not what I usually go for, but it''s an exception I''m glad I made.', TRUE, 40, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 275 DAY)),
(1004, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is an exceptional love letter to retro gaming. The monochrome graphics take me back to the days of early computer games, while its gameplay revolves around clever detective work instead of modern hand-holding and microtransactions. This isn''t just a game; it''s an experience that respects not only your time but also your wallet.', TRUE, 15, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 108 DAY)),
(1058, 30, 1, 'While others may praise its unique aesthetic, Return of the Obra Dinn left much to be desired for me. The gameplay felt tedious rather than engaging, and I found myself frustrated with the lack of straightforward progression. I expected more for my money, but instead, I felt like I was stuck on a ghost ship of disappointment.', FALSE, 7, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 87 DAY)),
(1049, 30, 2, 'Everyone was raving about how amazing Return of the Obra Dinn was, but I just don''t see it. The story seemed intriguing at first, but I quickly lost interest with its slow pacing and confusing puzzles. Maybe I bought into the hype too much because I ended up feeling let down and bewildered.', FALSE, 12, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 365 DAY)),
(1042, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a refreshing challenge for those who love a good mental workout. While it might not have the combat prowess of a Souls game, it requires a different kind of strategic thinking and persistence that I sincerely appreciate. If you enjoy pushing your deductive skills to the limit, this is a voyage worth taking.', TRUE, 11, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 91 DAY)),
(1041, 30, 4, 'From the moment Return of the Obra Dinn launched, I was hooked. The attention to detail and the intricacies of its narrative structure kept me engaged from start to finish. It''s clear that every aspect of this game was thoughtfully crafted, making it a must-play for anyone who appreciates innovation and storytelling in gaming.', TRUE, 6, 39, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 336 DAY)),
(1013, 30, 3, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a masterpiece of game design, but as a QA Tester, I found some areas that felt slightly unstable. The game''s intricate logic puzzles were impressive, but I couldn''t help but notice minor bugs within certain animations and sound triggers. Given the complexity of the game, these are understandable, yet a bit distracting. Overall, a solid experience, but it could use a patch or two for perfection.', TRUE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 273 DAY)),
(1007, 30, 3, 'I wanted to love Return of the Obra Dinn, really, I did. Everyone was talking about it, and I felt like I had to check it out to avoid FOMO. While the art style was striking and the story intriguing, it didn''t quite resonate with me. Perhaps it''s the slow pace or the lack of dynamic action that left me feeling a bit indifferent. It''s a good game, objectively, but just not for me.', TRUE, 10, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 99 DAY)),
(1023, 30, 4, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a fascinating experience, but I gotta say, it’s not exactly built for a speedrun. However, the delight of uncovering various glitches was an unexpected thrill! There were a few pathing quirks and some scene skips that offered a chance for speedrunning tricks. For those who love finding ways to beat games in unintended ways, there’s some potential here.', TRUE, 1, 98, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 350 DAY)),
(1028, 30, 2, 'As a controller devotee, Return of the Obra Dinn posed some challenges. The game is designed heavily around mouse-driven gameplay, which made navigation clunky on a controller. I spent more time wrestling with controls than solving the actual mysteries. It’s a shame because the story and art style are incredible, but it’s just not optimized for those of us who shun keyboards and mice.', FALSE, 12, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 43 DAY)),
(1026, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn took me back to the golden age of gaming with its retro-inspired graphics and innovative storytelling. It was a refreshing escape from the modern gaming landscape riddled with microtransactions. No ads, no in-game purchases, just pure, unadulterated gaming bliss. It’s a love letter to those of us who long for the simplicity and creativity of the past.', TRUE, 6, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1005, 30, 5, 'TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter): Return of the Obra Dinn is a masterpiece for those who love a solid single-player experience. The game''s achievements are crafted with care, encouraging players to uncover every last secret without the headache of grinding multiplayer nonsense. It''s a journey of clues, deductions, and revelations, all wrapped in a delightful monochrome package. Highly recommended for any achievement hunter who values their solo time!', TRUE, 37, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 82 DAY)),
(1034, 30, 5, 'EarlyAccessAce (The Alpha Tester): Return of the Obra Dinn feels like a meticulously crafted puzzle box. From the moment I started piecing together the fate of the ship''s crew, I was completely invested in its story and mechanics. The unique art style and atmospheric sound design create an engrossing experience. This game offers something fresh and innovative, making it a must-play for those who crave originality.', TRUE, 10, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 89 DAY)),
(1020, 30, 3, 'SaleSnub (The Refund Rager): Okay, so I get the hype around Return of the Obra Dinn, but it''s not for everyone. Yes, the graphics are unique, and the detective work can be rewarding, but if you''re looking for action or replayability, you might be disappointed. I finished it pretty quickly, and there''s not much incentive to return. For the price, I expected a bit more content.', TRUE, 0, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 214 DAY)),
(1000, 30, 4, 'FreeLootLurker (The F2P Leech): Return of the Obra Dinn doesn''t hide any content behind paywalls, so that''s a huge plus in my book. It''s a self-contained experience where everything is accessible from the start. The game relies heavily on your observational skills and wit rather than your wallet, which is refreshing in today''s gaming landscape. Overall, a captivating experience with no nasty surprises!', TRUE, 10, 46, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 189 DAY)),
(1014, 30, 5, 'PenguinPlayer (The Linux User): Finally, a game I can play on Linux without wrestling with anti-cheat software or compatibility layers! Return of the Obra Dinn runs smoothly on my setup, delivering an engaging mystery with style. It''s a brilliant example of how a well-designed game doesn''t need unnecessary anti-cheat measures to be enjoyable on our penguin-loving platform. Bravo!', TRUE, 5, 64, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 32 DAY)),
(1024, 30, 5, 'As a self-proclaimed Lore Archaeologist, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' is a treasure trove of enigmatic storytelling. The game masterfully weaves a narrative tapestry where every clue hints at a deeper mystery. The vague plot is not a detriment but a delight, encouraging inquisitive minds to dig and piece together the crew''s fate. It''s a masterpiece for anyone who revels in the art of uncovering stories hidden in shadows.', TRUE, 4, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 248 DAY)),
(1010, 30, 4, 'As the Competitive Tryhard, I have to say Obra Dinn stands out with its rigorously engaging puzzle design. No easy modes to hold your hand here, and the bittersweet satisfaction of piecing together the mystery of the ship is akin to the thrill of a well-fought victory. While the challenge is high, the eventual payoff is worth the cerebral effort. A game that respects its player''s intellect is always a win in my book.', TRUE, 2, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 221 DAY)),
(1044, 30, 3, 'From the standpoint of an Ultrawide User, Obra Dinn''s rigid field of view was a bit of a letdown. The game''s visuals, though artistically stunning with its 1-bit style, would have greatly benefited from more flexibility in the display options. Immersion is key, and while the story pulls you in, the constrained visuals pull you out of a truly expansive experience.', TRUE, 9, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 254 DAY)),
(1011, 30, 2, 'Caught in the wave of hype, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' initially seemed like the game everyone was buzzing about. Yet, as a victim of the hype, my expectations were not entirely met. The distinct art and intriguing concept are admittedly impressive, but the pacing felt as slow as a ship drifting at sea. For those expecting non-stop thrills, temper your excitement.', FALSE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 11 DAY)),
(1048, 30, 4, 'As someone who measures success in achievements, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' is refreshingly single-player focused. The absence of multiplayer achievements is a blessing, allowing for a gratifying solo experience. Each correctly identified crew member and solved mystery feels like unlocking a unique achievement worthy of the time invested. It''s proof that single-player games can deliver a fulfilling quest for completionists.', TRUE, 11, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 145 DAY)),
(1016, 30, 5, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): Return of the Obra Dinn is a flawless gem on the Steam Deck. This game runs seamlessly, making it a perfect pick for on-the-go gaming. The verified status is rightly deserved as the controls are intuitive and the performance has never once stuttered. Every detail of the ship feels alive, and solving mysteries while lounging comfortably with my Deck is a dream come true. A must-play for any Steam Deck owner!', TRUE, 8, 67, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1055, 30, 5, 'TimeMachine (The Nostalgia Goggles): Return of the Obra Dinn is a breath of fresh, old air. It has the magic of a bygone era where creativity triumphed over cash grabs. No in-game purchases to tarnish the experience—just pure, immersive storytelling. The monochrome style successfully harkens back to classic games, and the intricate puzzles are reminiscent of the adventures I adored in the past. This is how games should be made!', TRUE, 0, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 44 DAY)),
(1003, 30, 4, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): I didn''t expect much when unwrapping Return of the Obra Dinn, but wow! It''s like stepping into an interactive detective movie. The art style is unique, and the sound design pulls you right into the mysterious vibe. Though I wasn''t sure what I was getting into at first, I ended up playing for hours. A pleasant surprise for sure!', TRUE, 26, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 97 DAY)),
(1022, 30, 4, 'BossBattleBrute (The Souls Veteran): Return of the Obra Dinn isn''t about dodging attacks or mastering combat, but that doesn''t mean it lacks challenge. The difficulty lies in its complex puzzle mechanics and requiring a keen eye for detail. It’s a different kind of battle, one where your mind is the weapon. Any fan of intense challenges will find themselves lost in the pages of this pirate ship narrative.', TRUE, 6, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 336 DAY));